cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.IR. 

The paper deals with abnormal event detection in videos, which is a problem in computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a two-stage algorithm based on machine learning techniques such as k-means clustering and one-class SVM, which falls under the scope of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of deep appearance features extracted from a pre-trained neural network also suggests the possibility of the paper belonging to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper deals with video processing, which falls under the scope of cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper deals with outlier detection, which is a problem in information retrieval, suggesting the possibility of the paper belonging to cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
